result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Joseph J Hagenkord in court with attorney Katie Beth Bricco.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern, Becky Van Dam, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Dismissed and Read-in to: 13CF1528 and 13CM1653.

Defendant Joseph J Hagenkord in court with attorney Katie Beth Bricco.  Bryan C. Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense is looking into a global resolution.  Hearing scheduled for October 24, 2014 at 10:00 am.

Absolute sobriety, defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol.  Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant to report/comply with Wisconsin Community Services Pretrial Supervision Program.  Defendant to report within the first business day after posting bail or released from custody.  Defendant ordered to SCRAM monitoring.  Defendant to pay costs associated with SCRAM monitoring.  Defendants who can not  pay will be required to follow an enhanced level of direct supervision requirements as established by WCS.  WCS will notify the Court.

Defendant Joseph J Hagenkord in court, in custody, with attorney Katie Beth Bricco.   Bryan C. Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Officer David G. from the City of Waukesha was sworn and testified on behalf of the State. Court takes judicial notice of the pending file 13CF1528. Cross examination by the defense. State rests. No testimony by the defense. State moves for bind over and presents arguments. Defense counsel object to bind over. Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and binds the defendant over for trial.   NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED.  Defense presents bail arguments and requests a bail modification or huber bailee status. State objects to any modification. Court does not grant the modifcation of bail, but the court will  order SCRAM monitoring and allow HUBER BAILEE status for employment and to go the WCS to be placed on the SCRAM monitoring. 
  Hearing scheduled for September 8, 2014 at 03:00 pm.
